  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>potato</strong><strong>es&nbsp;</strong>(skins on)&nbsp;into large, bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Trim the <strong>green beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of salted boiling water and cook for 10 min or until almost fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;to another pot of <strong>salted</strong> water, bring to the boil and cook for 8 min</p>\r\n<p>Once done, cool the egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;by running them under cold water</p>\r\n<p>Tip: cooling the eggs completely makes them easier to peel!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>olives</strong> roughly</p>\r\n<p>Cut <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;</span>into wedges, then cut them in half&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> with&nbsp;3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> &nbsp;and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>dressing&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the <strong>potatoes</strong>, cover and remove from the heat</p>\r\n<p>Leave the pot off the heat for 4 min or until the potatoes are cooked&nbsp;and the beans are bright green and al dente (retaining a bite)</p>\r\n<p>Drain&nbsp;and return the potatoes and beans back to the pot, off the heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add&nbsp;a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> to the <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>beans</strong> and give everything a gentle mix</p>\r\n<p>Peel and quarter the cooled <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/556_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
